  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and guidelines against money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary international organization that sets standards and promotes effective implementation of legal, regulatory, and operational measures to combat money laundering. Many countries have adopted anti-money laundering (AML) regulations based on FATF recommendations, including:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence\n2. Reporting suspicious transactions\n3. Maintaining records of financial activities\n4. Implementing screening processes\n5. Cooperating with international law enforcement\n\nThe United Nations and various international treaties also provide frameworks for combating money laundering globally. Most developed countries have specific national laws and regulations to prevent and prosecute money laundering activities.",
